<Layout title="ISO 13485">

<Navbar />

<section class="hero">

<div class="container">

<span class="badge">
ISO Standard
</span>

<h1>
ISO 13485:2016
</h1>

<h2>
Medical Devices — Quality Management Systems
</h2>

<p>

ISO 13485 specifies the requirements for a Quality Management System
(QMS) where an organization needs to demonstrate its ability to
consistently provide medical devices and related services that meet
customer and regulatory requirements.

</p>

<a
class="official"
href="https://www.iso.org/standard/59752.html"
target="_blank"
>

Official ISO Page

</a>

</div>

</section>

<section class="content">

<div class="container">

<div class="card">

<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>

ISO 13485 is the internationally recognized Quality Management System
(QMS) standard specifically developed for the medical device industry.

Unlike ISO 9001, ISO 13485 focuses heavily on regulatory compliance,
risk management, product safety, traceability, validation,
documentation and maintaining product effectiveness throughout its
entire life cycle.

Medical device manufacturers across the world use ISO 13485 to
demonstrate compliance with regulatory requirements.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h2>Purpose</h2>

<ul>

<li>Establish an effective Quality Management System</li>

<li>Improve patient safety</li>

<li>Meet international regulatory requirements</li>

<li>Ensure product consistency</li>

<li>Support CE Marking</li>

<li>Improve customer confidence</li>

<li>Reduce product failures</li>

</ul>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h2>Who Should Use ISO 13485?</h2>

<ul>

<li>Medical Device Manufacturers</li>

<li>Contract Manufacturers</li>

<li>OEM Companies</li>

<li>Component Suppliers</li>

<li>Sterilization Facilities</li>

<li>Importers & Distributors</li>

<li>Regulatory Affairs Professionals</li>

<li>Quality Assurance Engineers</li>

<li>Clinical Evaluation Teams</li>

<li>Medical Device Startups</li>

</ul>

</div>
<div class="card">

<h2>Scope of ISO 13485</h2>

<p>

ISO 13485 applies to organizations involved in one or more stages of the
medical device life cycle. It covers design, development, production,
installation, servicing, storage, distribution and disposal of medical
devices and related services.

The standard can also be implemented by suppliers providing products or
services to medical device manufacturers.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h2>Main Clauses of ISO 13485</h2>

<table>

<tr>
<th>Clause</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Clause 4</td>
<td>Quality Management System</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Clause 5</td>
<td>Management Responsibility</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Clause 6</td>
<td>Resource Management</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Clause 7</td>
<td>Product Realization</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Clause 8</td>
<td>Measurement, Analysis & Improvement</td>
</tr>

</table>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h2>Benefits of ISO 13485</h2>

<ul>

<li>✔ International recognition</li>

<li>✔ Improved product quality</li>

<li>✔ Better regulatory compliance</li>

<li>✔ Easier CE Marking preparation</li>

<li>✔ Improved supplier management</li>

<li>✔ Better document control</li>

<li>✔ Strong CAPA system</li>

<li>✔ Reduced recalls</li>

<li>✔ Improved traceability</li>

<li>✔ Higher customer confidence</li>

</ul>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h2>Relationship with Other Standards</h2>

<table>

<tr>

<th>Standard</th>

<th>Purpose</th>

</tr>

<tr>

