<section class="faq">

<div class="container">

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-grid">

<div class="faq-card">
<h3>What is ISO 13485?</h3>
<p>
ISO 13485 is the international Quality Management System (QMS)
standard specifically developed for medical devices.
</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-card">
<h3>Is ISO 13485 mandatory?</h3>
<p>
Although not legally mandatory in every country,
it is expected by most regulators and certification
bodies worldwide.
</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-card">
<h3>Who should implement ISO 13485?</h3>
<p>
Medical device manufacturers, OEMs, contract
manufacturers, suppliers, importers and distributors.
</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-card">
<h3>Does ISO 13485 include Risk Management?</h3>
<p>
Yes. ISO 13485 requires integration with ISO 14971
throughout the product life cycle.
</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-card">
<h3>Can startups implement ISO 13485?</h3>
<p>
Absolutely. Implementing ISO 13485 from the beginning
helps startups prepare for regulatory approvals.
</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-card">
<h3>Where can I obtain the official standard?</h3>
<p>
Only through the official ISO website or authorized
national standards organizations.
</p>
</div>

</div>

</div>

